text:
My husband and I recently stayed at Origin Seminyak for 4 nights in a one bedroom pool villa. 
Pros: As always in Bali, the staff were amazing!!! Furnishing, style etc was beautiful and the bedroom and en suite were huge. Bed was large and comfy. Pool was clean and refreshing. If you want to be right in the thick of it in Seminyak, the location is great. Seminyak Square, restaurants and shopping are less than a 5 min walk and the beach is a 10 min walk.
Cons: I have stayed in many hotels and private villas over the years in Bali and what I love is that even when you are in the middle of the hurly burly the hotel or villa feels like an oasis. Unfortunately, our villa didn’t feel like this. Other buildings overlook the villa and it was right next to the gang/road with a not so high wall, so we could hear everything from outside the villa. The garden and pool area only gets morning sun, which was not an issue for us, but might be for others. The bedroom and upstairs bathroom also did not feel private as the other suites had a view in. It also felt that whoever had done the renovation (it seemed like an old building that had been refurbished rather than a new one) had gone with style over substance. Eg the bathroom looked stunning but the lighting was terrible. 
Overall, Origin was nice but you can find MUCH better value if you want a private pool villa.

text:
I just stayed for 4 nights in Origin in a 2 bedroom villa and there are allot of good things going for it and a number of issues with the villa itself which made the stay less than the 5 star I would have given it. 
My feedback is mainly on the design and the hardware of the villa itself btw.
1. This isn't exactly a negative but just an observation: It is big! There is a small pond of goldfish in the villa at the end where the staircase is leading up to 2nd floor. my family was a group of 5 ( 3 adults and 2 11-yr olds) and we felt that there are some design and layout oddities that didn't make it "flow" right. Now, this is very subjective as some families love the space and some don't. I am well aware of the floor plan before I booked it so I was prepared to be sleeping on the 2nd floor whilst my kids slept on the 1st but even the room on the 2nd floor is a bit out of proportion to the king size bed.  The 2nd floor bathroom is huge as in you could easily fit 10 adults or more in there. LOL  The sinks were positioned quite low in both bathrooms so if you are a tall person, you're gonna have some problems using it.
There are some very rough rugs also in the bathroom so don't go in barefoot. 
All in all, the space will be great for people who come in with loads of luggage or even surf boards as the outside corridor on the 2nd floor and the 1st floor have TONS Of open space for you to put big items like surf boards and big floaties.

2. The glass doors on the 2nd floor shower in the bathroom creaked whenever we open and closed it, the corners of all the mirrors look rusted or peeling. My 2nd floor bathroom toilet was also constantly wet so somewhere was leaking. Now, in recognition to the service, I had WA-ed them at about 9pm on the first day  to inform them the floor area neat the toilet bowl was wet all the time and they came to fix it the following day by putting silicon but it was still leaking from somewhere. This isn't a dealbreaker but one of the little things that showed that quality wasn't exactly part of the build.

3.  The water pressure was very inconsistent as sometimes it would flow and sometimes it trickled. I also gave feedback via WA ( same time as I mentioned about the wet toilet bowl) and in recognition of the service, they came to replace the water pump that was situated on the first floor near the pool the following day. It took about 1.5 hours for them to change the pump.

Basically, all the feedback i had given on the first night, was attended to the following day morning when their engineering team was at work. So thumbs up for that. 

4. There is no closed wardrobes, it's all open hanging type. No issues here but something to point out for others to take note.

5. Bfast is more or less the same daily but it's good enough. They are very on time for the bfast and will come in and set it up at the appointed time. There are about 5 choices of mains ( pancakes, a few  choices for eggs, museli, mee goreng), 2 types of fruit juice and fresh fruits/over night oats for sides. The origin staff will WA you the bfast menu and ask what time you would like to have it. Take note it starts from 8am

6. Service is a winner here. The staff are always willing to help and will attend to your issues when approached. WE borrowed a small kids board and a frisbee. And whenever I needed anything, I will just pop out to their office which is just outside to request for stuff like blowing up the donut floaty which they did. :) Thank you to all the staff at Origin. 

7. location of this place is a plus and yet a bane. It's VERY near Seminyak Square/Village and you can walk out easily to Eat Street , Kudeta, and PEttitingit beach which is so near as well as other cafes and restaurants.  VERY convenient. There is watsons/Guardian pharmacies nearby @ Seminyak Village. So all good. Now the bane is when it comes to getting a Taxi. This villa is located in a VERY SMALL ROAD (GG pandu) and if your driver miss it, they need to go 1 big round. The small road has a road sign but it's blocked by a pole so most drivers tend to miss this place. Only the motor bikes will be able to find it quickly so when I did a Grabfood in, the biker found this easy. But if you are gonna hail a taxi, I would say either walk out to Seminyak Square OR walk the other way and wait for a taxi in front of the main road Mini Mart or @ one of the resorts if calling a GOjek or a Grab, I called for a Grab and the guy stopped at the main road and didn't turn in. I took a video of the main road leading into the small road to send to my driver for the airport pick up so that he doesn't get lost. LOL

8. The villa also comes equipped with a Full sized fridge, AQUA water dispenser ( cold, hot and room temp water), sink and a coffee drip machine in the small kitchenette area. 

9. The living and dining area is not airconditioned so if you want a place with full aircon everywhere, this wont suit your needs. Only the bedrooms have the split unit aircon units. There is a ceiling fan for the sofa/living area but no fan for the dining table area which I think is a mistake. We are eating and kinda sweating at the same time. Perhaps install another ceiling fan for the dining area.

10. Staff will also come in the evenings to put mosquito coils on the 2nd floor corridor and ground floor to chase away the mossies. Good idea since it's all open concept. 

11. Kids loved the pool but take note, the pool is DEEP. It is about 1.2 or 1,4m then drop to 1,8 to 2m for about 2/3 of the entire length. So if you got small kids who can't swim, You need to keep an eye on them ALL THE TIME.

12. The outdoor wooden decking leading to the living areas from the main entrance are showing it's age  and I feel needs to be replaced soon. Some of the wooden panels are broken at the side.

13. FYI to all that Extra Bed without bfast is charged at 250K IDR/night inclusive of taxes.

All in all, this place has allot going for it just that the way the villa is designed, the hardware of it.. needs to be improved. Not everyone will appreciate the open concept of the place but it was a good stay for sure. I highly recommend this place for big groups of friends or families with teenagers as the space would def suit their needs.

text:
Checks out all the basics 

- close to the “Seminyak action” - F&B, shopping and enjoy a bit of space / traveling in groups

-  Walkable to Italian establishment La Lucciola, shopping in Seminyak Square, popular brunch Sistersfield-Boss Burger, Monsieur Spoon combination, Ku De Ta and money changers at every other corner

- rates are affordable! 

Not that great … 

It rained lot while I was there for 2 nights. 1 night in the upstairs studio 1 bedroom and 1 night in the 2 bedroom. The heavy rain and winds made the floors slippery and I had a fall. The outside areas got wet with strong winds as it is an open concept so it’s great to have a closed area for the bedrooms. There’s also a pond in each room (with fish) that is cute as there is fish food provided in the room for feeding but with small children that could mean some supervision… both for the ones getting fed and the feeders. 

Like alot of Bali, the staircase leading to the second floor units are steep and not for those with mobility issues. The units are quite close together and on first night, we could hear our neighbours playing music and talking late into the night. Good thing is there’s alot of space within our unit to retreat into. 

Service was friendly and practical - water can have a slightly off-putting smell and if it bothers you, brush your teeth with the in-house filtered water as I was informed by the staff when I checked in - I like that. Our flight was delayed and with the heavy rains we reached the hotel past midnight but the staff was waiting for us. 

breakfast is simple, served to your room. It’s good enough with fresh fruit juice and eggs you can choose how u want them. There’s a fridge to store your drinks and a small pantry to plate food. 

boutique villa concept. Means no lobby, no public seating area, no public dining, no 24 hour concierge, no public shared pool. Go elsewhere if you desire these. Locks are traditional keys but there’s a safe in every room. 

All in all, Origin Seminyak is a hotel I would personally not rave a lot about but it delivered as described and it is consistent with what the reviews are saying. warrants my five stars

text:
Good:
- Location: the main entrance is in a small back laneway. During the day it is a convenient 2 minute walk to Seminyak village.  However at night when it is completely dark and "grab" or "gojet" do not want to pick you up in the laneway you have to walk about 100m in a completely dark laneway which can be dangerous if walking alone
- Aircon in rooms are good enough
- Staff are friendly and helpful when asked

Bad:
- The main living room is open and has one fan. This means that during the day it is too hot to sit comfortably and at night there are too many mosquitos. This means that when you are at the villa you either have to be in the pool or stuck in the bedroom with the aircon turned on.
- Dirty: The main bedrooms, sheets and towels were clean. However the main living room couch, the bathroom and the pool could be improved. The shower has rocks along the perimeter that may have been nice when new, but are now mouldy. The pool water looks relatively clean and seems fine to swim in, however the perimeter of the pool has a significant amount of algae.
- Bad breakfast. Other reviews have said the breakfast is great, however I have to disagree. The food is timely, but much better breakfast can be had in one of the many close breakfast places in Seminyak like "Sisterfields" or "Monsieur spoon." Although they have a kitchen on the premise, it seems as if the food is prepared elsewhere and just heated up at the place. The Eggs Benedict came with cold eggs? and one morning the milk for coffee was curdled. The fruit however seems fresh.
- Lack of attention to detail: The staff are lovely when approached, but service seems lacking. For example on arrival, we were given cooling face towels. After we used them we placed them on a chair to be picked up. After 2 days sitting on the same chair we reminded the staff they could be taken. Another example is in the main open living areas there are mosquito coils. Despite the open planned living the staff do not come to turn them on each night and we had to go purchase our own lighters to light them
...

We initially booked this place because of the good location and the fact in the pictures the premise appeared new, however having stayed at the place for one week I would not recommend it to other travellers.

text: I have stayed in many villas all around Bali. Origin Villa is definitely one of the best in terms of location and service. I booked the 2 bedroom villa (Number 2) which is really beautiful. The smaller bedroom is on level one, same level as the living, dining, kitchen and the pool. The master bedroom with an en-suite bathroom is upstairs and is very spacious. My daughters are in their teens so it's perfectly fine for them to be separated from us. Do take note of safety concerns if you have younger kids. The pool is quite deep and it is just a few steps from the bedroom. Each bedroom comes with good air-conditioners which are essential in the afternoons. The water from the tap tasted like desalinated sea water. However, a water dispenser is provided in the kitchen. Choosing to stay in Seminyak means being near good restaurants, cafes, shopping and the beach. Origin Villa checks all these. Make sure the first place you dine at is La Lucciola. It is only 7 mins walk from the villa and it will start off your stay in Seminyak with a big sigh of contentment. The staff at the villa is truly amazing! Friendly and helpful. Keeps the villa spotless. Good breakfast that is different every day. Villa is very quiet at night despite its central location. Hardly any mozzies, lizards or bugs. So if you are not budget-conscious, Origin Villa is truly a wonderful place to stay at.

Location is fantastic! Short walk out to Neon Palms, Motel Mexicola, Seminyak Square and the beach. Yet despite being so central, it was very quiet at night. 

Staff are very helpful and can easily be reached by whatsapp. They also helped us with reservations at various restaurants and motorbike rental. 

We took the 4 room villa and the pool was very comfortably sized. We loved it so much that most of my photos are of the pool! 

Villa has a water dispenser, unfortunately they don't top it up automatically. We had to inform them when it's empty and wait for them to come and top it up. Would be great if they checked it periodically and topped it up automatically, or left us a spare bottle so we can top it up ourselves. That would be a more seamless experience in my opinion. There was a night that we ran out of water and had to go out to buy our own. Thankfully, the minimart is not too far away. 

Same thing happened for toilet paper. We ran out one night as they do not provide spares in the villa. Would appreciate if they left a spare roll for each toilet. 

Staff are still quite new (I think) as the villa started in Dec 2018 (we stayed end March 2019). So they seemed a little confused about some things. We waited around 20 min for coffee one morning, before we found out that they did not top up the water in the coffee machine, hence there was no coffee being brewed.

Breakfast is cooked in their kitchen and not in your villa.

All in all, mostly great, small errors here and there that can be easily fixed. 
Looking forward to my next stay here!

I have stayed twice with Origin Seminyak - which is the sister property of Origin Ubud. The design and interiors of the villa complex are amazing - from environmentally friendly amenities to beautiful sarongs hanging in your wardrobe for you; they have thought of everything. Even with the mini-bar, I love that they had gluten free nuts (which I have literally just chomped down).

The one bedroom suite I am in is really spacious - it must be around 600-700 sq ft so it's a very generous size. Located on the second floor it is also very private. You have a shower and bath tub, plus a private balcony area outside where you can watch tv and dine. Origin has room service for breakfast and lunch, and the food is also fantastic.

My favourite is the omelette for brekky and the tangerine juice! 

The location is also fantastic - you are 50m from Sisterfields, so literally a 3 min walk to Seminyak Mall and Eat street. 

But because you are tucked away in a quiet lane - there is no noise or the hustle and bustle of Seminyak. 

Also it is easy to head to Canggu as we are near Kudeta side.

For the 3 or 2 BR villas, the pools are very large and again space is very generous. My friends stayed in the 2 BR and I stayed in the 3 BR last trip.

Overall a lovely boutique villa complex with good service. Staff are warm and polished.

Highly recommend as its good value for what you pay and newly opened!

We were very impressed by our stay at Origin. The villas are very nicely renovated with quality furnishings and amenities. The living / dining room is open plan, bright and very spacious, and leads out to a big garden and pool deck, which is perfect for relaxing. We stayed as a couple, but the villas are so big you would not feel on top of each other if you stayed with a group of friends / family - we were very surprised at the size of the place. The staff are excellent, very friendly and eager to help out with any dinner reservations, directions, requests etc. 
There is a daily changing breakfast menu included, which had a great selection and was very tasty. The pantry has a large fridge, water dispenser and tea/coffee making facilities so you can keep your own food and drink on hand.

We walked everywhere as it is so well located to the shops, bars, restaurants and the beach, so no need to sit in traffic or barter with taxi drivers! Its less then 5 mins to the beach and even closer to shops. There is so much to do around Origin you would not get bored spending a long time here. After a day of exploring the area, the quiet villas are the perfect place to relax - It does not feel like you are in the center of Seminyak at all! We will definitely be coming back!
